# Accounting Rules (V2.1)

**Authority:** `00_architecture_authority.mdc` · **Detail:** `doc/ARCHITECTURE.md` § Financial Reporting

## General ledger

- **All GL writes** go through `FinancialPostingService` (`modules/accounting/services/`)
- Never write `journal_entries` / `journal_lines` from routes or domain services directly
- Use `JournalRepository` only from within posting services
- After posting: `emitFinancialPosted()` for real-time GL sync

## Posting domains (reference)

| Source | Service |
|--------|---------|
| Bills | `billJournalPostingService` |
| Invoices | `invoiceJournalPostingService` |
| Transactions | `transactionJournalPostingService` |
| PEV | `pevJournalPostingService` |
| Investor | `investorJournalPostingService` |
| Fiscal period close | `fiscalPeriodCloseService` |

## Accounting periods

- `accounting_periods.status` includes `locked`
- `FinancialPostingService` enforces period lock before any GL write
- Period close mutations: audit + `emitEntityEvent()`

## Shared financial core

- Source: `shared/financial-core/` → synced to `backend/src/financial/`
- Trial balance, journal ledger, validation, dimension scope — **never duplicate** in components or routes
- Edit shared source; run `npm run build:backend`

## Reconciliation

- `shared/financial-core/financialReconciliationEngine.ts`
- API: `modules/accounting/routes/financialReconciliationRoutes.ts`

## MUST NOT

- Direct GL SQL in route handlers
- Bypass period lock
- New calculation logic outside `shared/financial-core/`
- Edit AUTO-GENERATED `backend/src/financial/*.ts`
